quran[25]{c,v,t}:
  55,1,The Mercy-giving
  55,2,has taught the Reading
  55,3,created man
  55,4,taught him self-expression
  55,5,"The sun and moon [move along] like clockwork"
  55,6,shrubs and trees both bend in worship
  55,7,"while He has raised the sky up and placed scales [there]"
  55,8,so you may not skimp in weighing
  55,9,"Always measure accurately with [all]fairness and do not give short weight"
  55,10,The earth has He laid out for humanity
  55,11,"offering fruit, datepalms bearing blossoms"
  55,12,"grain wrapped up in husks, and fragrant herbs"
  55,13,So which of your Lord´s benefits will both of you deny
  55,14,He created man from ringing clay just as a potter does
  55,15,while He created sprites from the glow in fire
  55,16,So which of your Lord´s benefits will you both deny
  55,17,Lord of both Easts and Lord of both Wests
  55,18,So which of our Lord´s benefits will both of you deny
  55,19,He has loosed both seas which still come together
  55,20,between them lies an isthmus which neither tries to cross
  55,21,So which of your Lord´s benefits will both of you deny
  55,22,He produces pearls and coral from them both
  55,23,so which of our Lord´s benefits will both of you deny
  55,24,His are the vessels looming up like landmarks on the sea
  55,25,so which of our Lord´s benefits will both of you deny